article.headline: Oakland 69, Centenary 68
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. (AP) -- Derek Coleman's three-pointer with 10.4 seconds gave Robert Morris a 69-68 victory over Central Connecticut Saturday. Coleman's shot extended Robert Morris' winning streak to four and ended its three-game losing streak to Central. Aaron Thomas led the Colonials (12-10, 9-4 Northeast Conference) with 18 points. Chaz McCrommon had 17 and Maurice Carter and Mark Anderson each scored 10. The Colonials shot 54.2 percent (26-48). Justin Chiera's 16 points paced Central (9-11, 6-7), which had its four-game winning streak snapped. Ron Robinson contributed 15 and Javier Mojica added 13 points and a game-high 10 rebounds. Robert Morris shot 8-11 to start the game to jump to a 24-12 lead. But four Chiera 3-pointers in the final 3:24 fueled a Blue Devils' comeback. His final one from 25 feet at the horn tied the score at 37-37 at halftime. Robinson scored five points, as Central went ahead 50-44 with just under 13 minutes remaining. But the Colonials stayed close until Coleman hit the game-winner from the top of the key. Central inbounded the ball and called a timeout with 5.4 seconds remaining. Lenny Jefferson then missed a shot in the lane. Robinson's 3-point attempt from the left corner bounced off the rim at the buzzer.
